$ Registry: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Policies\Microsoft\Edge
@ HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Policies\Microsoft\Edge

{ DefinePreferredLanguages

  The value of `DefinePreferredLanguages` influences the `Accept-Langague` → development/web/HTTP/header[HTTP header].

  It seems that this settings does not work well with q values (such as "en,en-US;q-09,.."), rather, it assigns `q` values.
  -
  With the following setting, the Accept-Language will be set to `en,en-US;q=0.9,de;q=0.8,de-CH;q=0.7,de-DE;q=0.6`:
code {
set-itemProperty 'HKCU:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Edge' DefinePreferredLanguages 'en,en-US,de,de-CH,de-DE'
code }


}
